Hair Salon Web Application
This is a web application for managing hair salon appointments. It allows users to book appointments, view past and future reservations, and modify or cancel them.

Technologies Used:

- ASP.NET MVC: Framework for developing web applications based on the model-view-controller architecture.
- Entity Framework: Object-Relational Mapping (ORM) to interact with the database.
- C#: Object-oriented programming language used for application development.
- MimeKit and MailKit: Libraries for handling and sending emails via SMTP.
- HTML, CSS, JavaScript: Used for the front-end of the application.
- Instructions for Cloning the Project:

Option 1: Clone Directly from GitHub

1) Go to the GitHub repository page.
2) Click on the "Code" button and choose "Open in Visual Studio."

Option 2: Download ZIP from GitHub

1) Go to the GitHub repository page.
2) Click on the "Code" button and choose "Download ZIP."
3) Extract the ZIP content to the desired folder.
4) Enter the folder titled "HairSalon."
5) Launch the "HairSalon.sln" file with Visual Studio.


IMPORTANT
Email Credentials Configuration
Before running the project, open the "Email.cs" file in the "Models" folder.
On line 18, insert the specific password: "muyt nvwv uutm efeh."

DATABASE BACKUP

Locate the backup folder: C:\Program Files\Microsoft SQL Server\MSSQL16.SQLEXPRESS\MSSQL\Backup
Place the file named "HairSalon.bak" inside the backup folder.

Now the project is ready to be explored and customized! Launch the application and start managing your hair salon reservations.

